Deputy National Security Advisor Antony Blinken met with Slovak Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign Minister Miroslav Lajcak to discuss the situation in Ukraine. They emphasized the importance of U.S. and EU support for Ukraine's sovereignty and territorial integrity, as well as the Ukrainian government's efforts to implement democratic reforms. They also agreed that Russia should withdraw its forces from Ukraine, stop supporting separatists, and fulfill its commitments under the Minsk cease-fire and peace plan agreements.